===Etymology 1===
Anglo Saxon ''felt''; akin to Dutch ''[[vilt]]'', German ''[[Filz]]'', and possibly to Greek hair or wool wrought into felt, Latin ''[[pilus]]'' hair, ''[[pileus]]'' a felt cap or hat.

====Noun====
'''felt''' ([[uncountable]])

#A [[cloth]] or stuff made of [[mat]]ted [[fibre]]s of [[wool]], or wool and [[fur]], [[full]]ed or wrought into a compact substance by rolling and pressure, with lees or size, without spinning or weaving.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*It were a delicate stratagem to shoe A troop of horse with '''felt'''. &mdash; Shakespeare, ''King Lear, IV-vi''
#A [[hat]] made of felt. &mdash; [[Thynne]]
#{{obsolete}} A [[skin]] or [[hide]]; a [[fell]]; a [[pelt]].

=====Quotations=====
*To know whether sheep are sound or not, see that the '''felt''' be loose &mdash; [[Mortimer]]

